  <td class="diff-context"><div>By 1869, Ancaster was a Village in the Township of Ancaster County Wentworth with a population of 500.  Mr. K. Thuresson turned out [[Carding|card clothing]]. The Ancaster Knitting Company employed over 100 in the manufacture of knitted goods. Messrs. H &amp; A Egleston manufactured agricultural implements, cotton and woolen machinery. Mr. A Egleston employed 20 in woolen and cloth mills.&lt;ref&gt;The province of Ontario gazetteer and directory. H. McEvoy Editor and Compiler, Toronto : Robertson &amp; Cook, Publishers, 1869&lt;/ref&gt;</div></td>
  <td class="diff-marker">&#160;</td>
  <td class="diff-context"><div>By 1869, Ancaster was a Village in the Township of Ancaster County Wentworth with a population of 500.  Mr. K. Thuresson turned out [[Carding|card clothing]]. The Ancaster Knitting Company employed over 100 in the manufacture of knitted goods. Messrs. H &amp; A Egleston manufactured agricultural implements, cotton and woolen machinery. Mr. A Egleston employed 20 in woolen and cloth mills.&lt;ref&gt;The province of Ontario gazetteer and directory. H. McEvoy Editor and Compiler, Toronto : Robertson &amp; Cook, Publishers, 1869&lt;/ref&gt;</div></td>
